Create new variables for each factored character variable

# Create lists of the factored levels
listCut <- as.data.frame(levels(diamonds$cut), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
colnames(listCut) = "levels"
listCut$lev2 <- c("Fair","Good","VeryGood","Premium","Ideal")
listColor <- levels(diamonds$color)
listClarity <- levels(diamonds$clarity)

# Separate out the Cut levels into separate binary columns
listCut
##      levels     lev2
## 1      Fair     Fair
## 2      Good     Good
## 3 Very Good VeryGood
## 4   Premium  Premium
## 5     Ideal    Ideal
diamonds <- diamonds %>% 
  transform(fcutFair = ifelse(diamonds$cut == listCut$levels[1], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcutGood = ifelse(diamonds$cut == listCut$levels[2], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcutVeryGood = ifelse(diamonds$cut == listCut$levels[3], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcutPremium = ifelse(diamonds$cut == listCut$levels[4], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcutIdeal = ifelse(diamonds$cut == listCut$levels[5], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(totalCut = fcutFair + fcutGood + fcutVeryGood + fcutPremium + fcutIdeal)

# Separate out the Color levels into separate binary columns
listColor
## [1] "D" "E" "F" "G" "H" "I" "J"
diamonds <- diamonds %>% 
  transform(fcolD = ifelse(diamonds$color == listColor[1], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcolE = ifelse(diamonds$color == listColor[2], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcolF = ifelse(diamonds$color == listColor[3], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcolG = ifelse(diamonds$color == listColor[4], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcolH = ifelse(diamonds$color == listColor[5], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcolI = ifelse(diamonds$color == listColor[6], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fcolJ = ifelse(diamonds$color == listColor[7], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(totalCol = fcolD + fcolE + fcolF + fcolG + fcolH + fcolI + fcolJ)

# Separate out the Clarity levels into separate binary columns
listClarity
## [1] "I1"   "SI2"  "SI1"  "VS2"  "VS1"  "VVS2" "VVS1" "IF"
diamonds <- diamonds %>% 
  transform(fclarI1 = ifelse(diamonds$clarity == listClarity[1], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fclarSI2 = ifelse(diamonds$clarity == listClarity[2], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fclarSI1 = ifelse(diamonds$clarity == listClarity[3], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fclarVS2 = ifelse(diamonds$clarity == listClarity[4], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fclarVS1 = ifelse(diamonds$clarity == listClarity[5], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fclarVVS2 = ifelse(diamonds$clarity == listClarity[6], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fclarVVS1 = ifelse(diamonds$clarity == listClarity[7], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(fclarIF = ifelse(diamonds$clarity == listClarity[8], 1, 0)) %>% 
  transform(totalClar = fclarI1 + fclarSI2 + fclarSI1 + fclarVS2 + fclarVS1 + fclarVVS2 + fclarVVS1 + fclarIF)

# Check if any levels are double-counted
nrow(filter(diamonds, totalCut > 1))
## [1] 0
nrow(filter(diamonds, totalCol > 1))
## [1] 0
nrow(filter(diamonds, totalClar > 1))
## [1] 0
